%h3 An example form, with a fieldset

%form
  %fieldset
    %legend Enter your details:

    %dl
      %dt
        %label Name:
      %dd
        %input{ :type => 'text' }

      %dt 
        %label Email:
      %dd
        %input{ :type => 'text' } 
        = icon 'email'
      %dd.notes
        We even correctly validate emails with '+' in, unlike 99% of the web!

      %dt
        %label Description:
      %dd
        %textarea

      %dt
      %dd.buttons
        %button.positive{ :type => 'submit' }
          = icon 'tick'
          Submit
        %a{ :href => "#" }
          = icon 'cog'
          Check form
        %a.negative.secondary{ :href => "#" }
          = icon 'cross'
          Cancel
  
    %p Correctly cleared after the end of the form.

%h3 Rails form error styles

%form  
  #errorExplanation
    %h2 Form could not be submitted
    %p Some elements of the submitted form were unable to pass our checks.
    %ul
      %li Name can't be blank.
      %li Email must be a valid email address.
    %p Some elements of the submitted form were unable to pass our checks.

  %dl
    %dt
      %label.fieldWithErrors Name:
    %dd
      %input.fieldWithErrors{ :type => 'text' }

    %dt 
      %label.fieldWithErrors Email:
    %dd
      %input.fieldWithErrors{ :type => 'text' } 
      = icon 'email'
